race.description: Barmah Park Restaurant & Cellar Door Mdn Plate
race.comment: GRAND MILLESIME (5) brought a string of sharp jumpouts was beaten a whisker on debut over 1203m at Kyneton. That's good form and she will be fitter and maps well. In a top barn and will take beating. CAFFETTIERA (1) also debuted in better company, producing a nice effort  beaten 1.3L at Geelong. She's also in a gun metro stable and jumps from a good draw. Has to be followed up. EDEN ROSE (3) ran below expectations last time at Pakenham, but was only beaten 1.4L at Moonee Valley first-up prior. Has a key gear switch and has plenty up the sleeve. A solid each-way proposition. GRAYNITA (7) has won a couple of jumpouts and gets the inside draw so keep safe on debut.
